p  he began his career as a securities analyst at halcyon investments  mr matlin holds a jd from the law school of the university of california at los angeles  and a bs in economics from the wharton school of the university of pennsylvania  mr matlin serves on the boards of directors of portfolio companies flagstar bank calatlantic group inc and is also a director of matlin  partners acquisition corporation mr matlin serves on the investment committee of matlinpatterson global advisers peter schoels managing partner peter schoels is managing partner of matlinpatterson and is the portfolio manager of matlinpatterson’s control and illiquid investments prior to joining matlinpatterson at inception in july  mr schoels was a vice president of credit suisse’s global distressed securities group investing in north america latin america western and eastern europe  prior to joining credit suisse mr schoels was a director of finance and strategy of itim group plc  previously mr schoels was manager of mergers and acquisitions for ispat international nv now arcelormittal which specialized in buying distressed steel assets globally  mr schoels holds an mba from ubi in brussels belgium  and a ba in international business from eckerd college st petersburg florida  mr schoels serves on the boards of directors of portfolio companies flagstar bank calatlantic group inc crescent communities and is also a director of matlin  partners acquisition corporation mr schoels serves on the investment committee of matlinpatterson global advisers robert weiss partner general counsel robert weiss is a partner and general counsel of matlinpatterson and general counsel of matlin  partners acquisition corporation prior to joining matlinpatterson in october  mr weiss was managing director at deutsche asset management responsible for hedge fund and fundoffunds administration accounting and productrelated legal and compliance functions  prior to deutsche asset management mr weiss was general counsel to moore capital management inc  and senior vice president within the futures and managed futures business of lehman brothers  and associate general counsel  mr weiss began his career in the legal department of futures commission merchant johnson matthey  wallace inc in  mr weiss holds a jd from hofstra law school  and an ab cum laude from vassar college  catherine frey partner catherine frey is a partner of matlinpatterson prior to joining matlin patterson in april  ms frey founded frey capital advisors llc focused on raising institutional capital for alternative investment managers in the leveraged loan and distressed and high yield corporate debt markets  prior to founding frey capital ms frey was an executive director at morgan stanley  and a managing director at bear stearns  specializing in the institutional distribution of high yield and distressed securities ms frey began her career in investment banking at donaldson lufkin  jenrette  and drexel burnham lambert  ms frey holds a bse from the wharton school at the university of pennsylvania  sherry gao chief financial officer sherry gao is chief financial officer of matlinpatterson and matlin  partners acquisition corporation prior to joining matlinpatterson in november  ms gao was a senior associate at deloitte  touche llp in the assurance practice specializing in private equity and hedge funds  –  ms gao is a certified public accountant in the state of new york ms gao holds a mba in finance from the new york university stern graduate school of business  and a ba in accounting from pace university  home    copyright   matlinpatterson global advisers llc all rights reserved use of this website is governed by the terms and conditions partner login  matlinpatterson about history investment philosophy differentiating factors client composition investment strategies global opportunities matlin  partners securitized credit teams corporate global opportunities matlin  partners securitized credit credit investment solut